# Grammar: hexa-lang self/raw_loader.hexa (same syntax as .raw / .loop / .chain).
# Source-of-truth for README.md governance under mk2. Predecessor mk1 .own (881L, 32 rules)
# retired 2026-05-03 commit 442afa7b. This file restores ONLY the 5 README-bound rules,
# preserving each rule as a separate concern (sealed / english / drift x2 / toolkit-table)
# rather than collapsing — concern separation outweighs hive raw.mk2 arch.001 collapsing
# benefit when rules touch different invariant axes.
#
# ============================================================
# P0 PRIORITY: own#29 readme-friendly-toolkit-required (HARD)
#
# This rule is the ALIEN-GRADE ALIGNMENT SSOT. The 7-column toolkit table format
# (🛸 alien-grade-reach / Tool / One-liner / Everyday analogy / What it does /
# <Mainstream> contrast / Doc) anchors n=6 master identity (own#2) directly in the
# Mainstream contrast cell — see Fusion §L116 precedent ("σ(6)=12-archetype unified
# lattice", "τ(6)=4-state full-cycle plant") and Chip §L147 precedent ("σ²=144 SM × τ=4 pipe ×
# φ=2 issue", "σ·J₂=288 / bank in-place compute"). README structure preservation is the
# user's most-critical invariant per 2026-05-04 directive ("이 구성에 가장중요!!!!").
# ============================================================
