#   own#29 toolkit-table    PARTIAL -- biology-only standalone tool/own29_readme_friendly_toolkit_lint.hexa; multi-section dispatcher tool/own_doc_lint.hexa --rule 29 reads mandatory-sections from this .own.readme (FU-2 verifies wiring)

own 14 live "readme-sealed-required — root README.md sealed hash mandatory (HARD warn ramp)"
  slug readme-sealed-required
  decl .readme-rules.json README.md.sealed.hash README.md tool/readme_sealed_check.hexa
  scope root README.md must keep `.readme-rules.json scopes.root.require_sealed=true` AND `README.md.sealed.hash` synchronized with shasum -a 256 README.md. Body edits without hash refresh forbidden.
  status live
  since 2026-05-04
  why .readme-rules.json scopes.root.require_sealed=true + README.md.sealed.hash present + tool/readme_sealed_check.hexa wired in .github/workflows/ci.yml:393. Sealed hash defends auto-generated blocks (toolkit tables / counts) from silent drift. Current sealed hash (293a8865...) verified MATCH actual sha256 at 2026-05-04 audit.
  invariant `.readme-rules.json` scopes.root.require_sealed = true
  invariant `README.md.sealed.hash` = sha256:<64-hex>; lower-case hex; 1 line
  invariant verify-tool: tool/readme_sealed_check.hexa exit 0 = match-or-init / 1 = mismatch / 2 = error
  cognitive-frameworks own#1 (doc-english-required, deps)
  cognitive-frameworks own#17 (public-readme-english-only, sister-rule)
  enforce hexa tool/readme_sealed_check.hexa
  ci-wiring .github/workflows/ci.yml:381-393 (readme-sealed-hash job)
  cron on-commit
  on_fail block
  exit-codes 0=PASS / 1=mismatch / 2=error
  label own#14 readme-sealed-required (live, actively wired)

