own 20 live "readme-techniques-count-drift — README techniques count matches actual hexa file count (daily warn)"
  slug readme-techniques-count-drift
  decl README.md techniques/
  scope README.md `<N> Techniques` token must equal `find techniques -name '*.hexa' -type f ! -name 'test_techniques*' | wc -l`. Drift -> warn (daily cron), not block.
  status live
  since 2026-05-04
  why Migrated from mk1 loop-rules.json#1 (2026-04-21). Prevents doc-vs-fact drift; keeps README count in sync with disk reality. Audit 2026-05-04: README L208 `**225 Techniques**` = actual 225 hexa files -> MATCHED.
  drift_doc README.md
  drift_pattern (\d+) Techniques
  drift_actual find techniques -name '*.hexa' -type f ! -name 'test_techniques*' | wc -l
  cognitive-frameworks own#14 (sealed-hash, sibling-rule)
  cognitive-frameworks own#21 (tests-count-drift, sibling-rule)
  cron daily
  on_fail warn
  label own#20 readme-techniques-count-drift (live, MATCHED at audit)

