own 29 live "readme-friendly-toolkit-required — README friendly toolkit table 7-column generalized across 32 mandatory sections (HARD, P0)"
  slug readme-friendly-toolkit-required
  decl README.md tool/own_doc_lint.hexa tool/own29_readme_friendly_toolkit_lint.hexa
  scope HARD block — README.md per-section friendly toolkit table contract. Each section in mandatory-sections list MUST contain: H2 heading match + 7-column header (🛸 alien-grade reach FIRST cell; <Mainstream> contrast variation per section) + ≥min_rows data rows + each row first cell integer 0..999 + each row last cell `[doc](domains/<axis>/<slug>/<slug>.md)` resolving via test -f. P0 PRIORITY: this rule is the alien-grade alignment SSOT — n=6 master identity (own#2) anchored directly in Mainstream contrast cell per Fusion/Chip precedent.
  status live
  since 2026-05-04
  why README.md mk1 governance accumulated dense technical tables (cycle 14-22) -> friendly Molecular Toolkit (HEXA family) 6-column block (cycle 25) -> generalized multi-section spec (cycle 25 strengthening) -> 🛸 alien-grade-reach prepended as first column making 7-column header (cycle 29 strengthening 2026-04-29 per user "외계인 지수 / 현재 도달지수 / 🛸 이모지 단독 / lint 반드시 필요"). mk2 reconstruction adds Pets + Apps as 31st + 32nd mandatory-sections (README has Pets at L539 + Apps at L570; mk1 .own had only 30). User directive 2026-05-04: "이 구성에 가장중요!!!!" — toolkit table structure preservation = top priority.
